1
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:54,034
I was in a forest.

2
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:57,559
I couldn't find my way.

3
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:00,913
I was hopelessly lost.

4
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:06,840
It kept getting darker.

5
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,553
I started to panic.

6
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:13,079
I thought,
I'll never find my way again.

7
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,271
UNDER THE RAINBOW

8
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:18,231
And then... I see a man,

9
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:19,350
stock still,

10
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:22,120
looking at me,
with so much kindness.

11
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:25,278
He reaches out,
and I go to him, without thinking.

12
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:27,835
And someone is behind him.
Like an angel.

13
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:29,553
He <i>is</i> an angel.

14
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:31,399
Pointing at him.

15
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,873
He carries me up and away.

16
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:39,036
Wait, the angel carries you?

17
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:40,750
No, the man.

18
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:42,837
Then he and I are flying.

19
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:46,553
On a horse, but a weird one,
with a bird's head.

20
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:47,796
A hippogriff.

21
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:51,356
A horse with a bird's head.

22
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:53,233
It's called a hippogriff.

23
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,034
So we're flying,

24
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:58,672
flying over the countryside.

25
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:01,713
And suddenly I felt great.
I was confident.

26
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:03,793
All my fear was gone.

27
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,798
And we fly over my home,

28
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:08,373
and I see my dad as tiny.

29
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:09,775
Really tiny!

30
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:12,932
Waving his arms, yelling to me.

31
00:03:13,060 --> 00:03:14,574
Not that way!

32
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:17,930
Not that way!

33
00:03:18,620 --> 00:03:19,940
"Not that way!"

34
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,679
Stop that, Lauranie!

35
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,075
Give me those...

36
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:26,438
...wands.
This is not a game.

37
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:29,758
Look! Now it's broken.
It won't work anymore!

38
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:33,476
And the flowers, the pumpkins!
I'm not picking them up!

39
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,917
Mathieu, Lulu! You hear me?

40
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:41,854
Nina is so absorbed.

41
00:03:41,980 --> 00:03:44,495
Stock still,
totally into her book.

42
00:03:44,620 --> 00:03:46,213
Yeah, it's the Bible.

43
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:48,214
- The Bible?
- Yes.

44
00:03:48,340 --> 00:03:50,809
Every chance she gets,
she reads the Bible.

45
00:03:51,260 --> 00:03:53,536
- Your dream?
- That's all I remember.

46
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:56,810
It's idiotic, but I was thinking...

47
00:03:57,580 --> 00:04:00,778
there's a chance
it will never happen to me.

48
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:02,916
What?

49
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,553
I woke up and I thought,

50
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,433
I've never really felt that.

51
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:09,870
I've never been carried away
like that.

52
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:12,478
I've never really loved. I...

53
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:14,831
never really loved someone.

54
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:18,633
It got me so depressed.

55
00:04:19,280 --> 00:04:22,273
Come on,
you're so young, you have time!

56
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,352
Nothing but bad luck lately.

57
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:29,039
Yeah, what can you do?

58
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,160
I had the 4 and the 11.

59
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:33,351
4th time in a row I had 2.

60
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:37,112
That's the trifecta.
You need 3, that's the whole point.

61
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:41,271
Anyway,
there are more dire things.

62
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,110
Right.

63
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:49,037
- My condolences, Pierre.
- Thank you.

64
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:57,476
You hadn't seen your dad
in how long?

65
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:00,160
I was just wondering that,
last night.

66
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:01,430
I don't know...

67
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,840
2 or 3 months, I guess.

68
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,993
I feel nothing.

69
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:08,794
I hadn't seen him in ages,
but it affects me.

70
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:12,197
Affects you.
Because you decided it would.

71
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:14,039
My father was nothing to you.

72
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:17,756
He was not nothing to me.
What does that mean?

73
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:20,955
Don't exaggerate.

74
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:24,355
He's your dad.
He was always there for Sandro.

75
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:26,517
And he was very shaken.

76
00:05:27,740 --> 00:05:28,730
Where is Sandro?

77
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,717
Did you ask him about the deposit?

78
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:48,199
I didn't get a chance.

79
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,753
We buried someone. You notice?

80
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:52,075
What deposit?

81
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,156
Well...

82
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:56,399
I either live at Mum's till I'm 50,
or rent a place.

83
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:57,670
Pierre!

84
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:01,311
Oh, I loved your father so!

85
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:03,272
- Be strong, OK?
- Yeah.

86
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:05,153
You can still talk to him.

87
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,273
He hears you.

88
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,392
- You'll talk to him?
- Sure.

89
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:11,637
In any case, you'll see him soon.

90
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:17,020
- You must speak to him.
- Yes, I will.

91
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,575
That's good.

92
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:24,455
Madame Irma. She still exists?

93
00:06:25,380 --> 00:06:26,450
Apparently.

94
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:28,136
And still sick.

95
00:06:30,660 --> 00:06:32,219
You remember the date?

96
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:34,620
Date?

97
00:06:34,740 --> 00:06:36,220
Of your death, remember?

98
00:06:36,340 --> 00:06:37,535
Come on!

99
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:40,615
How should I remember that crap?

100
00:06:40,740 --> 00:06:42,015
Date of your death?

101
00:06:42,140 --> 00:06:43,733
No, it's horseshit.

102
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:46,580
A crazy lady
who used to do everyone's horoscope.

103
00:06:46,700 --> 00:06:48,054
It's nonsense.

104
00:06:48,660 --> 00:06:50,458
So... when is it?

105
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:52,734
I said I can't recall.

106
00:06:52,860 --> 00:06:55,091
I can. It made an impression on me.

107
00:06:55,980 --> 00:06:59,610
Not that I believe it.
Sure, it's horseshit but...

108
00:06:59,740 --> 00:07:01,094
it makes an impression.

109
00:07:02,820 --> 00:07:04,174
There they are, I'm off.

110
00:07:04,940 --> 00:07:07,694
You're off?
Aren't you coming to Odette's?

111
00:07:07,820 --> 00:07:09,413
Certainly not.

112
00:07:09,540 --> 00:07:12,135
Come by the office,
talk about the deposit?

113
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:16,974
- Your girlfriend has kids?
- As you can see.

114
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:19,100
Can't be fun for you.

115
00:07:19,220 --> 00:07:20,449
No, it isn't.

116
00:07:25,660 --> 00:07:27,094
I'm parked at the corner.

117
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:53,216
Pull it up!

118
00:07:53,380 --> 00:07:55,815
Pull the handle up,
the thingy will fall.

119
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:58,176
This is great.

120
00:07:59,540 --> 00:08:01,691
Enough room for a vegetable garden.

121
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:05,259
You said a tiny garden.
It's not so tiny.

122
00:08:09,540 --> 00:08:11,293
No, don't drink the water!

123
00:08:11,940 --> 00:08:13,613
It's supposedly drinkable, but...

124
00:08:13,740 --> 00:08:16,858
Which reminds me,
Eric said he might stop by.

125
00:08:16,980 --> 00:08:20,257
Tell him the water's back,
but it's brown.

126
00:08:21,380 --> 00:08:23,133
Nina, I'm leaving!

127
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:26,209
That's my mum, I'm not taking it.

128
00:08:26,340 --> 00:08:27,979
Did her operation go well?

129
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:30,217
Hands aren't easy, I'm told.

130
00:08:30,340 --> 00:08:31,820
That's her again.

131
00:08:31,940 --> 00:08:34,455
If I answer,
we'll just argue as usual.

132
00:08:35,380 --> 00:08:36,530
Nina!

133
00:08:37,340 --> 00:08:41,619
She won't say goodbye.
The Red Sea must be parting.

134
00:08:42,580 --> 00:08:43,616
You free Saturday?

135
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:46,820
Not Saturday.
That's the Princes' Ball.

136
00:08:46,940 --> 00:08:49,580
- You never showed me your dress.
- Right!

137
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:51,259
Actually, there are two.

138
00:08:51,380 --> 00:08:53,372
I loved them, so I got both.

139
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:56,296
I don't really want to go.

140
00:08:56,820 --> 00:08:57,810
Why?

141
00:08:57,940 --> 00:09:00,978
Your dream might be an omen.
You could meet someone.

142
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:03,296
That's exactly
what Mrs Bérard said.

143
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:05,539
Is she your fortune teller?

144
00:09:05,660 --> 00:09:07,538
Well, she's a radiesthesist.

145
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:10,854
Hello, Ma'am.
A survey on the fears of the French.

146
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:12,380
No, thanks!

147
00:09:14,140 --> 00:09:15,460
Hello. A survey...

148
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:18,470
The crisis.

149
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,398
This is a time of crisis.

150
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,034
Terrorism.

151
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:24,949
Unemployment.

152
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,636
Poverty, disease.

153
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,514
Like I said, the climate.

154
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,040
It's all mixed up.

155
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:35,153
Winter in summer,
summer in winter.

156
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:37,880
Summer in winter.

157
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:41,195
Well, thanks.

158
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:42,640
You're welcome.

159
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:50,854
I'm not working enough.

160
00:09:51,820 --> 00:09:54,619
I have to work on the recital!
My goddamn father!

161
00:09:54,740 --> 00:09:56,538
What's he got to do with it?

162
00:09:56,660 --> 00:10:00,290
Here I am doing stupid surveys.
Will he lift a finger?

163
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:03,396
He runs a driving school.
Is he rich?

164
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,034
No, but...

165
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:08,756
My grandfather just died.
Left him money, he could help.

166
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:11,315
Every single time,
I have to beg him.

167
00:10:14,260 --> 00:10:17,458
For the deposit,
I have to get on my knees.

168
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:20,452
The grandfather you liked?

169
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:31,310
Going to the party?

170
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,510
What party?

171
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,871
The princes' ball, on Saturday.

172
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,992
I have a quintet rehearsal.

173
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,634
Shit, you're rehearsing.

174
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:40,160
Why? You're going?

175
00:10:41,740 --> 00:10:43,572
Well I don't know...

176
00:10:44,220 --> 00:10:45,734
I won't know anyone.

177
00:10:47,020 --> 00:10:48,659
Julien's brothers got comps.

178
00:10:48,780 --> 00:10:51,420
Frankly,
I don't feel like going but...

179
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:53,816
Without you...

180
00:10:53,940 --> 00:10:56,774
They might finish early.
I could meet you there.

181
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,632
I was sure you were going.

182
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:03,351
I'll try to skip a movement.

183
00:11:16,940 --> 00:11:18,215
Could totally suck.

184
00:11:18,340 --> 00:11:21,094
It could always totally suck.
Why do anything?

185
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:22,654
Just come and see.

186
00:11:22,780 --> 00:11:24,658
- Got to go!
- Later!

187
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:28,490
You know them, it's your milieu.
I don't.

188
00:11:28,620 --> 00:11:30,100
I'll feel like an idiot.

189
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:32,496
My milieu? Don't go overboard.

190
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:34,213
You're not from the jungle.

191
00:11:34,340 --> 00:11:37,333
And you have to dress.
I don't own a suit.

192
00:11:38,860 --> 00:11:41,534
You don't need one.
Got a black jacket?

193
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:44,698
Anyway, on Saturdays
I have to pick up my mum.

194
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:46,176
Pick up your mum?

195
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:48,815
She works Saturday nights.
I drive her home.

196
00:11:49,820 --> 00:11:52,130
She's afraid she'll get mugged.

197
00:11:52,260 --> 00:11:55,094
So at midnight, in any case,
I'll have to split.

198
00:12:11,860 --> 00:12:13,374
Where's your dad?

199
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:16,456
He's in the cemetery.

200
00:12:16,580 --> 00:12:18,333
When does he go to heaven?

201
00:12:18,460 --> 00:12:19,655
Heaven? No.

202
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:22,296
No, he'll stay in the cemetery...

203
00:12:22,820 --> 00:12:25,460
- Morgane, eat your carrots.
- I'm eating them!

204
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:29,139
Are you going to die?

205
00:12:29,260 --> 00:12:31,855
Sure, one day. We all die.

206
00:12:31,980 --> 00:12:33,414
So when do you die?

207
00:12:33,540 --> 00:12:34,815
I have no idea.

208
00:12:34,940 --> 00:12:36,090
Enough, Johanna.

209
00:12:36,220 --> 00:12:37,495
Doesn't bother me.

210
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:40,692
Stop, you'll break your glass!

211
00:12:40,820 --> 00:12:42,459
Eat your vegetables.

212
00:12:42,580 --> 00:12:43,650
I'm eating them!

213
00:12:43,780 --> 00:12:45,851
Will you go to heaven when you die?

214
00:12:45,980 --> 00:12:47,972
You don't go to heaven when...

215
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:51,013
You stay in a sort of...

216
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,239
Like... Like in a box.

217
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:56,872
Can't hear myself talk!

218
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,640
- Got any olive oil?
- On the right.

219
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:02,878
It's not the body.
The spirit goes to heaven.

220
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,231
And there you meet
everyone you knew.

221
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:08,114
People think you go to heaven,
because they need

222
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:09,879
to believe in an afterlife.

223
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:10,990
But no.

224
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:14,636
You turn into a skeleton.
You've seen those before, right?

225
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:16,991
The skin goes and the bones remain.

226
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:19,476
Personally, I think we go to heaven.

227
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:23,150
The truth is, no one knows.
You do as you see fit.

228
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:27,397
Put that glass down!

229
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:29,872
No way I drink that water!

230
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,799
Or even wash with it.
Washing with brown water!

231
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:34,673
It's not dirty, it's rust.

232
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,837
I don't wash with rust.

233
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,076
It won't last.

234
00:13:38,680 --> 00:13:40,558
There you go. It works.

235
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,957
For more heat, press here.

236
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,150
Minus, plus.

237
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:47,517
This button. Minus, plus.

238
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:50,156
Got it?

239
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,957
If it turns off... It won't.

240
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:56,232
But if it does,
press here, with the flame.

241
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:58,033
I'll never remember.

242
00:13:58,160 --> 00:13:59,150
Fine.

243
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:02,676
Well, I'll say goodbye to Nina.

244
00:14:05,860 --> 00:14:07,180
Yeah, I remember.

245
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:09,257
He's the first one who...

246
00:14:09,780 --> 00:14:12,170
Isn't John the Baptist
from Jesus' family?

247
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:15,850
No! Jesus has no family.
Even his parents aren't his parents.

248
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,096
Oh I see.

249
00:14:17,740 --> 00:14:20,778
- Know what "Jesus" means?
- Tell me Tuesday.

250
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:22,539
It means "saviour".

251
00:14:24,980 --> 00:14:26,778
She keeps scratching. Notice?

252
00:14:28,220 --> 00:14:29,574
She never stops.

253
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:31,532
Then sometimes not at all.

254
00:14:32,060 --> 00:14:33,779
It's very psychosomatic.

255
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:37,316
Right. Everything is psychosomatic.

256
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:39,318
Well everything is!

257
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:42,478
I didn't say it,
the dermatologist did.

258
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:47,554
I don't get it. I clicked OK.

259
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:50,320
And it says to enter my code again.

260
00:14:52,260 --> 00:14:53,455
Enter it.

261
00:14:54,140 --> 00:14:55,335
All right.

262
00:14:55,940 --> 00:14:57,135
I enter it...

263
00:14:59,260 --> 00:15:01,331
And it says "incorrect code".

264
00:15:01,460 --> 00:15:04,214
I don't know.
Maybe you spelled it wrong.

265
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:07,412
Wait, I know.
It might be another one.

266
00:15:07,540 --> 00:15:09,372
What? You have several codes?

267
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,014
Sure! I have a code for...

268
00:15:12,140 --> 00:15:14,894
Why? Use one code!
I only have one code.

269
00:15:15,020 --> 00:15:17,171
Shit, that one didn't work either!

270
