538
00:37:16,760 --> 00:37:20,754
As far as I know, frankly,
he wasn't particularly traumatised.

539
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:22,997
However you bring them up is wrong.

540
00:37:23,120 --> 00:37:26,352
Excuse me,
I must tell my husband something.

541
00:37:26,480 --> 00:37:28,949
I turn around and I see Sandro,
staring back

542
00:37:29,380 --> 00:37:31,497
with an angel pointing him out.

543
00:37:31,620 --> 00:37:34,818
Because there was this statue
behind him, a finger

544
00:37:34,940 --> 00:37:36,090
pointing at him.

545
00:37:36,820 --> 00:37:38,573
The fortune teller said that?

546
00:37:38,700 --> 00:37:40,453
No, it was my dream.

547
00:37:40,580 --> 00:37:42,890
I see,
but the fortune teller said it.

548
00:37:43,380 --> 00:37:46,532
She's not a fortune teller,
but yes she said it.

549
00:37:47,380 --> 00:37:50,134
You remember
I didn't want to go to that party.

550
00:37:50,260 --> 00:37:52,092
I remember. Do you?

551
00:37:52,620 --> 00:37:53,895
Girl's totally nuts.

552
00:37:54,020 --> 00:37:56,979
Come on...
But how old is her mother?

553
00:37:57,100 --> 00:37:58,170
That's her mother?

554
00:38:00,380 --> 00:38:02,940
You're the fairest of them all.
As usual.

555
00:38:03,580 --> 00:38:06,573
Don't bother.
My father believes in nothing.

556
00:38:06,700 --> 00:38:09,169
This is verified. They're facts.

557
00:38:09,300 --> 00:38:11,815
Facts... They're coincidences.

558
00:38:11,940 --> 00:38:13,260
Anyway, anyway...

559
00:38:14,540 --> 00:38:16,372
what we wanted to say is...

560
00:38:17,880 --> 00:38:20,349
we're getting engaged on...

561
00:38:21,680 --> 00:38:23,114
March 14th.

562
00:38:24,500 --> 00:38:26,969
We had said the 13th,
but it was a Friday.

563
00:38:45,700 --> 00:38:47,054
I was wondering,

564
00:38:47,180 --> 00:38:49,058
is there some medicine...?

565
00:38:50,300 --> 00:38:51,620
No connection.

566
00:38:52,460 --> 00:38:55,931
But since I have these thoughts
that keep coming back,

567
00:38:56,060 --> 00:38:58,655
I thought maybe
there's some drug to...

568
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:02,152
get rid of them, stop them.

569
00:39:04,160 --> 00:39:05,640
What kind of thoughts?

570
00:39:08,560 --> 00:39:10,199
Not the thoughts themselves.

571
00:39:10,320 --> 00:39:13,597
It's how they keep coming back,
all the time.

572
00:39:16,040 --> 00:39:19,636
Listen,
I can't help, I'm a podiatrist.

573
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:23,117
But I know a good therapist.
Want his address?

574
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:25,593
No, I was just asking.

575
00:39:26,860 --> 00:39:27,896
No, I'm fine.

576
00:39:28,740 --> 00:39:29,890
It's just...

577
00:39:31,180 --> 00:39:34,298
I'm a little tense right now.
That can't help.

578
00:39:36,180 --> 00:39:37,933
I got people at the house.

579
00:39:38,860 --> 00:39:39,850
Tiresome...

580
00:39:40,340 --> 00:39:43,333
Yes. Getting back to your feet,
the soles.

581
00:39:44,060 --> 00:39:46,370
Wear them every day,
or the pain returns.

582
00:40:00,740 --> 00:40:02,254
Isn't love beautiful?

583
00:40:02,380 --> 00:40:03,894
I'm not objective.

584
00:40:04,020 --> 00:40:05,136
Meaning?

585
00:40:11,380 --> 00:40:12,416
Really?

586
00:40:13,260 --> 00:40:14,330
I get it.

587
00:40:15,900 --> 00:40:17,619
I didn't know.

588
00:40:22,340 --> 00:40:24,138
I meant it ironically.

589
00:40:24,260 --> 00:40:26,217
I don't think love is so great.

590
00:40:27,180 --> 00:40:30,856
Some detail you get attached to,
fabricating a myth.

591
00:40:32,700 --> 00:40:35,056
- Don't you agree?
- Not at all.

592
00:40:35,180 --> 00:40:36,580
Of course not.

593
00:40:39,600 --> 00:40:41,592
I must not be very perceptive.

594
00:40:42,320 --> 00:40:43,640
I didn't see a thing.

595
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:45,353
No one saw a thing.

596
00:40:48,580 --> 00:40:50,651
Think you'll be destroyed for long?

597
00:40:51,700 --> 00:40:54,010
Lots of charming guys around,
you know?

598
00:40:54,140 --> 00:40:56,735
- Like you?
- Yes, good example.

599
00:40:56,860 --> 00:40:58,658
- You don't believe in love.
- No.

600
00:40:58,780 --> 00:41:01,534
But... I believe in friendship.

601
00:41:01,660 --> 00:41:03,379
I hate seeing you like that.

602
00:41:22,760 --> 00:41:24,160
Kiss her already!

603
00:41:26,420 --> 00:41:30,175
What did we say?
I tap my wand and he turns into...?

604
00:41:30,300 --> 00:41:32,860
- Prince Charming.
- Right, and kiss her!

605
00:41:36,080 --> 00:41:38,640
Come on, not this again.

606
00:41:38,760 --> 00:41:41,559
You wanted to be Prince Charming
and now...

607
00:41:41,680 --> 00:41:44,878
you won't kiss her.
That's not charming, sorry!

608
00:41:45,700 --> 00:41:47,612
You too! Everybody!

609
00:41:47,740 --> 00:41:50,653
Get into character!
You have to believe a little!

610
00:41:51,180 --> 00:41:52,580
Lulu, same thing!

611
00:41:52,700 --> 00:41:55,659
Each time you offer the apple,
you look apologetic.

612
00:41:56,500 --> 00:41:59,220
You're a witch.
So act like a witch a little!

613
00:41:59,340 --> 00:42:01,218
I don't like being a witch.

614
00:42:01,640 --> 00:42:03,791
Oh? What do you want to be?

615
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:04,910
A tree.

616
00:42:05,040 --> 00:42:06,156
A tree?

617
00:42:12,740 --> 00:42:13,935
Get to the right.

618
00:42:14,860 --> 00:42:16,931
Right. Right!

619
00:42:17,060 --> 00:42:18,779
Get to the right! The right!

620
00:42:22,740 --> 00:42:25,050
Excuse me, I'm sorry. Sorry.

621
00:42:25,680 --> 00:42:27,319
OK, we're all right, but...

622
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:30,114
when I grab the wheel,
you have to let me.

623
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:32,277
You fought me, you can't fight.

624
00:42:32,400 --> 00:42:34,232
- I'm sorry.
- Sorry!

625
00:42:39,440 --> 00:42:42,080
How long has it been
since you drove?

626
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:43,714
I don't know, 10 years.

627
00:42:43,840 --> 00:42:46,071
Sure, but even then,
it was the same.

628
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:47,395
I was paralysed.

629
00:42:47,520 --> 00:42:49,113
I thought I was more mature.

630
00:42:50,240 --> 00:42:52,880
That I'd be more at ease.
But it's like before.

631
00:42:53,700 --> 00:42:56,010
I'm paralysed... terrified.

632
00:42:56,440 --> 00:42:57,954
No reason to be terrified.

633
00:42:58,080 --> 00:43:00,800
There is!
I keep feeling I'm going to die.

634
00:43:00,920 --> 00:43:02,400
Or else kill people.

635
00:43:04,720 --> 00:43:05,756
It's a fantasy.

636
00:43:05,880 --> 00:43:07,109
I understand.

637
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:10,229
A fantasy, but that's just it.

638
00:43:10,680 --> 00:43:11,909
It is a fantasy.

639
00:43:12,400 --> 00:43:14,357
You can't always just submit.

640
00:43:14,480 --> 00:43:16,472
Take control, we're not children.

641
00:43:16,600 --> 00:43:18,956
We must be capable
of taking control.

642
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:22,390
Right.

643
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:24,512
That's what I'm trying to do.

644
00:43:27,360 --> 00:43:30,159
Maybe acupuncture,
at the same time, could help.

645
00:43:30,280 --> 00:43:31,794
Maybe it will relax me.

646
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:36,156
Well, in any case, thanks.

647
00:43:36,600 --> 00:43:38,512
For dropping me off.

648
00:43:38,640 --> 00:43:40,711
No problem, it's on my way.

649
00:43:42,840 --> 00:43:45,674
- See you Thursday?
- Right. Thursday.

650
00:43:47,880 --> 00:43:51,237
- Sure you won't have coffee?
- No, I'm fine. Thanks.

651
00:43:51,860 --> 00:43:53,499
See? That's my car.

652
00:43:57,700 --> 00:43:58,850
See you Thursday.

653
00:43:58,980 --> 00:44:00,175
Thursday.

654
00:44:41,340 --> 00:44:42,330
Excuse me...

655
00:44:46,700 --> 00:44:48,293
Excuse me, I'm lost.

656
00:44:48,420 --> 00:44:50,935
I'm going to Rue des Acacias.
Lost my way.

657
00:44:51,060 --> 00:44:52,972
Rue des Acacias?
I'm going there.

658
00:44:53,100 --> 00:44:54,500
Can I drop you?

659
00:44:55,120 --> 00:44:56,793
No. Thank you, but...

660
00:44:56,920 --> 00:44:59,480
I wanted to walk. I've been there,

661
00:44:59,600 --> 00:45:00,795
but I always drove.

662
00:45:00,920 --> 00:45:02,513
Now I'm completely lost.

663
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:04,036
All right.

664
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:07,231
It depends
what you expect from life.

665
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:10,799
If you want to go fast,
no time to lose,

666
00:45:11,240 --> 00:45:15,075
if you know exactly what you want,
it's straight ahead, then right.

667
00:45:16,820 --> 00:45:22,452
But if you're more of a dreamer,
open to the unknown, a thinker,

668
00:45:22,580 --> 00:45:23,855
that way.

669
00:45:24,620 --> 00:45:27,260
It's longer, but much prettier.

670
00:45:27,820 --> 00:45:29,698
It's called "Needle Way".

671
00:45:33,060 --> 00:45:34,096
Well thanks.

672
00:45:34,220 --> 00:45:35,449
Don't mention it.

673
00:45:41,440 --> 00:45:43,716
I'm waiting to see which way you go.

674
00:46:01,740 --> 00:46:03,174
I got totally lost.

675
00:46:03,300 --> 00:46:06,213
I cut through the woods.
I got all turned around.

676
00:46:06,340 --> 00:46:08,980
Fortunately,
this guy straightened me out.

677
00:46:10,220 --> 00:46:11,654
He wanted to drive me.

678
00:46:13,120 --> 00:46:15,271
He was strange. Know what he said?

679
00:46:15,400 --> 00:46:17,278
This corkscrew is impossible.

680
00:46:18,040 --> 00:46:19,110
Hello.

681
00:46:20,280 --> 00:46:22,158
Was it pretty? Like the walk?

682
00:46:23,260 --> 00:46:25,013
You know each other?

683
00:46:26,380 --> 00:46:29,100
He's the one.
The man who gave me directions.

684
00:46:30,700 --> 00:46:32,896
This is Maxime. My neighbour.

685
00:46:33,380 --> 00:46:34,530
I mentioned him.

686
00:46:34,660 --> 00:46:36,731
Laura, my darling niece.

687
00:46:36,860 --> 00:46:37,816
Laura...

688
00:46:38,460 --> 00:46:39,894
Want some wine?

689
00:46:40,020 --> 00:46:41,090
Sure.

690
00:46:52,620 --> 00:46:53,736
I'll go, Marianne.

691
00:46:53,860 --> 00:46:55,010
You can stay.

692
00:46:55,140 --> 00:46:56,654
I have to go anyway.

693
00:46:57,260 --> 00:46:59,820
A pleasure, Laura.
Maybe see you soon?

694
00:46:59,940 --> 00:47:01,294
Yes, maybe.

695
00:47:02,340 --> 00:47:06,414
Tomorrow your life changes.
You'll have a 21st-century corkscrew.

696
00:47:06,540 --> 00:47:08,020
One that unscrews corks.

697
00:47:13,340 --> 00:47:14,740
Thanks for the extension cord!

698
00:47:19,860 --> 00:47:20,896
He's great.

699
00:47:21,540 --> 00:47:23,418
You know he's in music?

700
00:47:23,540 --> 00:47:25,213
Really? What does he do?

701
00:47:25,340 --> 00:47:27,696
I don't know,
I didn't really get it.

702
00:47:27,820 --> 00:47:30,176
I know he writes articles.

703
00:47:30,700 --> 00:47:32,578
Critiques... I don't know.

704
00:47:32,700 --> 00:47:35,818
And he works for a festival.
Or an orchestra.

705
00:47:35,940 --> 00:47:38,250
I can't recall, but he's in music.

706
00:47:40,760 --> 00:47:41,876
Funny.

707
00:47:42,400 --> 00:47:44,198
- Pretty, right?
- Yeah.

708
00:47:52,000 --> 00:47:53,912
"Hi, Mum! Hi, Laura!"

709
00:47:54,040 --> 00:47:55,110
How are you, Laura?

710
00:47:59,200 --> 00:48:01,192
I have no idea what's wrong.

711
00:48:01,320 --> 00:48:04,950
It's been 2 hours.
She won't talk, won't answer.

712
00:48:05,600 --> 00:48:07,956
The Bible's not doing her any good.

713
00:48:08,080 --> 00:48:09,639
I'll go say hello.

714
00:48:14,340 --> 00:48:17,777
In any case,
I know when this shit got into her.

715
00:48:21,160 --> 00:48:25,154
Well then, please Eric, let's do it.
Let's at least try.

716
00:48:25,280 --> 00:48:28,796
- We'll go see Devaux, the 3 of us.
- No, please.

717
00:48:28,920 --> 00:48:30,798
What's so terrible?

718
00:48:31,320 --> 00:48:32,754
What are you afraid of?

719
00:48:32,880 --> 00:48:34,553
I'm afraid of nothing.

720
00:48:35,280 --> 00:48:39,354
I won't go see some guy
with his own ideas about parenting

721
00:48:39,480 --> 00:48:42,439
so he can drum us full
of his personal morality! What a bore!

722
00:48:42,560 --> 00:48:44,552
You don't know, you never tried.

723
00:48:46,340 --> 00:48:48,172
And this is for Nina.

724
00:48:48,300 --> 00:48:50,860
Not for you.
I'm not trying to convince you.

725
00:48:52,540 --> 00:48:53,530
Try.

726
00:48:54,180 --> 00:48:56,137
A shrink can tell me nothing new.

727
00:48:58,860 --> 00:49:02,058
It's our separation
that Nina can't stand.

728
00:49:06,280 --> 00:49:09,352
Are you doing so much better
since you started therapy?

729
00:49:12,080 --> 00:49:13,434
Yes, I'm doing better.

730
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:17,154
<i>Hundreds of dead fish.
Utter devastation.</i>

731
00:49:17,280 --> 00:49:20,079
<i>Local people all point
to upriver Casseul Industries,</i>

732
00:49:20,200 --> 00:49:21,873
<i>saying they fill these waters</i>

733
00:49:22,360 --> 00:49:23,714
<i>with toxic waste.</i>

734
00:49:23,840 --> 00:49:25,274
<i>CEO Guillaume Casseul</i>

735
00:49:25,400 --> 00:49:28,950
<i>denies his company had a role
in this ecological disaster,</i>

736
00:49:29,080 --> 00:49:32,278
<i>but the company stock price
took a plunge...</i>

737
00:49:33,300 --> 00:49:34,450
Mum?

738
00:49:36,100 --> 00:49:38,854
Mum, could I take this
to Dad's tomorrow?

739
00:49:38,980 --> 00:49:40,255
You're not going.

740
00:49:40,380 --> 00:49:43,498
He called.
He can't. Something came up.

741
00:49:49,760 --> 00:49:50,750
Come on.

742
00:49:50,880 --> 00:49:54,635
I mentioned it, I didn't call him.
It just came up.

743
00:49:55,160 --> 00:49:56,435
He'll feel obliged.

744
00:49:56,560 --> 00:50:00,315
He'll think I put you up to it.
I don't care if he comes!

745
00:50:00,440 --> 00:50:01,999
Hardly knows I make music!

746
00:50:02,420 --> 00:50:04,537
And if it's so he can scowl

747
00:50:05,060 --> 00:50:07,416
like at the Legion of Honour,
no thanks!

748
00:50:07,540 --> 00:50:09,497
I said it just came up.

749
00:50:09,620 --> 00:50:12,738
I said Sandro's concert is soon.
I didn't say to come.

750
00:50:13,580 --> 00:50:15,060
"Sandro's concert."

751
00:50:15,500 --> 00:50:17,696
What? It's not your concert?

752
00:50:17,820 --> 00:50:20,096
It's a finals recital.

753
00:50:20,580 --> 00:50:22,651
There are others. It's not just me.

754
00:50:22,780 --> 00:50:26,820
I say "Sandro's concert," too.
We don't care about the others.

755
00:50:27,740 --> 00:50:29,493
Did Laura hear it already?

756
00:50:29,620 --> 00:50:30,770
Did she like it?

757
00:50:30,900 --> 00:50:34,177
He won't let me. He wants me
to hear it fresh, in concert.

758
00:50:34,300 --> 00:50:35,939
Directly at the concert?

759
00:50:36,360 --> 00:50:38,716
Of course, Mum. No comparison!

760
00:50:39,360 --> 00:50:41,477
I'll be finished in two minutes.

761
00:50:42,600 --> 00:50:44,239
Where do we meet after?

762
00:50:45,700 --> 00:50:46,656
My place?

763
00:50:48,020 --> 00:50:49,090
Your place?

764
00:50:49,820 --> 00:50:51,334
Your place is better.

765
00:50:51,460 --> 00:50:53,258
My place?
My place.

766
00:50:55,040 --> 00:50:58,158
She sees herself
in a pretty white dress, that's why.

767
00:50:58,800 --> 00:51:01,838
Sure, but...
that's incidental.

768
00:51:02,640 --> 00:51:05,030
Lots of girls
want a first communion.

769
00:51:06,080 --> 00:51:07,514
It's not about that.

770
00:51:11,820 --> 00:51:13,573
The move maybe.

771
00:51:13,700 --> 00:51:14,690
Maybe.

772
00:51:16,180 --> 00:51:17,500
As I see it,

773
00:51:18,060 --> 00:51:20,700
I'm hearing about a girl
who's not with us.

774
00:51:21,380 --> 00:51:23,099
Who isn't concentrating.

775
00:51:26,300 --> 00:51:27,859
You know, when children...

776
00:51:27,980 --> 00:51:31,940
when they feel things are
a little... unstable,

777
00:51:33,160 --> 00:51:35,117
they need to find reassurance.

778
00:51:36,280 --> 00:51:38,078
I was recently separated.

779
00:51:45,140 --> 00:51:47,450
But it's fine. Everything's fine...

780
00:51:48,380 --> 00:51:50,895
For the child,
I certainly hope so.

781
00:52:22,580 --> 00:52:23,650
By the way,

782
00:52:24,380 --> 00:52:25,734
I thought it over.

783
00:52:26,300 --> 00:52:27,495
I'm OK with it.

784
00:52:28,140 --> 00:52:29,574
You're OK with what?

785
00:52:30,420 --> 00:52:31,649
What you wanted.

786
00:52:32,960 --> 00:52:34,633
How you wanted us to be.

787
00:52:35,960 --> 00:52:37,280
To be freer.

788
00:52:37,880 --> 00:52:40,395
I'm OK with it.
You're right.

789
00:52:43,920 --> 00:52:45,354
Want us to try?

790
00:52:46,880 --> 00:52:48,439
To get back together?

791
00:52:58,620 --> 00:52:59,895
You don't love me anymore.

792
00:53:00,020 --> 00:53:03,616
Don't. I'll always love you.
That's not the point.

793
00:53:18,860 --> 00:53:20,089
Sorry, I'm no good.

794
00:53:20,220 --> 00:53:22,098
No big deal, we're alive.

795
00:53:22,220 --> 00:53:24,860
No, I can't even drive.

796
00:53:24,980 --> 00:53:27,654
I can't even...
I'll never drive again.

797
00:53:28,080 --> 00:53:31,391
You can drive.
Just check the rear-view mirror.

798
00:53:31,880 --> 00:53:33,917
I'll give you a manual, for review.

799
00:53:34,040 --> 00:53:36,077
My husband did the driving.

800
00:53:36,400 --> 00:53:38,073
He didn't want me to drive.

801
00:53:38,300 --> 00:53:40,371
He was right. We nearly died!

802
00:53:40,600 --> 00:53:42,114
It's your second lesson.

803
00:53:42,800 --> 00:53:45,838
I wanted only to be alone,
to be independent.

804
00:53:46,260 --> 00:53:47,580
It was my dream.

805
00:53:48,060 --> 00:53:49,414
Now I realise...

806
00:53:50,660 --> 00:53:52,413
I need help with everything.

807
00:53:53,180 --> 00:53:55,137
I'm handicapped, it's horrible.

808
00:53:56,860 --> 00:53:58,658
I have to re-learn everything.

809
00:53:59,220 --> 00:54:00,449
It sucks to be alone.

810
00:54:00,580 --> 00:54:02,936
No, don't say that.
It's wonderful.

811
00:54:03,940 --> 00:54:05,420
The peace of mind.

812
00:54:06,740 --> 00:54:09,653
No obligations, no negotiations.
No noise.

813
00:54:12,320 --> 00:54:13,276
Well...

814
00:54:14,320 --> 00:54:15,436
Should we go?

815
00:54:15,560 --> 00:54:17,711
Ignition, signal, rear-view.

816
00:54:18,700 --> 00:54:19,690
Are you sure?

817
00:54:20,300 --> 00:54:21,814
We can't stay here.

818
00:54:21,940 --> 00:54:23,340
You don't want to drive?

819
00:54:23,460 --> 00:54:24,894
I already know how.

820
00:54:25,020 --> 00:54:26,136
We almost died!

821
00:54:28,100 --> 00:54:30,615
No. I'm not supposed to die today.

822
00:54:32,180 --> 00:54:33,136
You're not?

823
00:54:36,240 --> 00:54:37,959
When are you supposed to die?

824
00:54:38,080 --> 00:54:39,309
March 14th.

825
00:54:42,480 --> 00:54:44,756
- This year?
- This year, yes.

826
00:54:46,080 --> 00:54:47,275
Really?

827
00:54:50,420 --> 00:54:52,173
Just a note of levity.

828
00:54:52,300 --> 00:54:54,212
This astrologer, a madwoman...

829
00:54:54,340 --> 00:54:56,172
told me that 40 years ago.

830
00:54:57,460 --> 00:54:59,452
They never say the date of death.

831
00:54:59,580 --> 00:55:02,379
They see it, but they don't tell.
I'm surprised!

832
00:55:02,500 --> 00:55:03,820
Well I don't care.

833
00:55:03,940 --> 00:55:06,250
Fortune-teller ethics don't matter to me.

834
00:55:06,380 --> 00:55:08,053
I really don't care.

835
00:55:08,180 --> 00:55:09,375
Ready to go?

836
00:55:12,300 --> 00:55:13,450
They have no right.

837
00:55:13,580 --> 00:55:15,537
Yeah, I know. But I don't care.

838
00:55:21,740 --> 00:55:22,730
Ignition.

839
00:55:28,860 --> 00:55:30,010
Signal.

840
00:55:32,160 --> 00:55:33,355
Rear-view.

841
00:55:34,600 --> 00:55:37,115
No, the rear-view
is to see behind you.

842
00:57:26,260 --> 00:57:28,138
- Bravo again!
- Thank you.

843
00:57:28,260 --> 00:57:29,250
- Call me?
- Sure.

844
00:57:29,380 --> 00:57:31,815
- I was so embarrassed.
- I didn't hear it.

845
00:57:31,940 --> 00:57:33,613
Like it?

846
00:57:33,740 --> 00:57:35,971
It was remarkable. Quality writing!

847
00:57:36,100 --> 00:57:37,420
Look. Behind you.

848
00:57:39,460 --> 00:57:40,576
The composer?

849
00:57:41,900 --> 00:57:42,970
Maxime Wolff.

850
00:57:43,100 --> 00:57:44,454
I know who you are.

851
00:57:44,580 --> 00:57:46,014
Your work is great.

852
00:57:47,900 --> 00:57:51,371
I'll leave you to your friends.
But here's my card.

853
00:57:51,900 --> 00:57:52,936
This is my card.

854
00:57:53,580 --> 00:57:54,775
Call me.

855
00:57:54,900 --> 00:57:56,812
I'd like to discuss an idea.

856
00:57:56,940 --> 00:57:57,930
All right.

857
00:58:00,800 --> 00:58:03,918
Laura, why are you here?
Are you lost again?

858
00:58:04,040 --> 00:58:05,520
No, not this time.

859
00:58:05,640 --> 00:58:07,472
Too bad, I can't help you.

860
00:58:08,120 --> 00:58:09,190
See you round?

861
00:58:09,840 --> 00:58:11,035
- See you?
- Yes.

862
00:58:13,840 --> 00:58:14,830
You know Wolff?

863
00:58:15,600 --> 00:58:18,399
- Did you know he was coming?
- No, I didn't!

864
00:58:18,840 --> 00:58:21,071
- Incredible. What luck.
- You knew?

865
00:58:21,200 --> 00:58:22,270
No, I didn't know!

866
00:58:22,400 --> 00:58:23,595
Is he famous?

867
00:58:27,480 --> 00:58:29,597
What do we do first?

868
00:58:29,720 --> 00:58:32,554
We put our stuff away!
That's right!

869
00:58:34,320 --> 00:58:36,437
What is it? Why the long face?

870
00:58:36,960 --> 00:58:38,872
Why are you frowning? Simon.

871
00:58:39,000 --> 00:58:41,959
Want to be a squirrel,
if you won't kiss her?

872
00:58:42,480 --> 00:58:44,312
She's the one who won't.

873
00:58:44,920 --> 00:58:46,479
Really? Why?

874
00:58:46,600 --> 00:58:48,398
She doesn't love me anymore.

875
00:58:53,040 --> 00:58:54,520
We'll see, no big deal.

876
00:58:54,640 --> 00:58:56,120
It is a big deal.

877
00:58:57,780 --> 00:58:59,055
No, listen...

878
00:59:00,740 --> 00:59:02,094
We'll think it over...

879
00:59:02,820 --> 00:59:04,459
we'll work it out.

880
00:59:05,460 --> 00:59:08,259
- I don't know...
- Can I be a dog?

881
00:59:08,740 --> 00:59:09,890
Sure, yeah...

882
00:59:10,020 --> 00:59:12,535
Well, is there a dog in the show?

883
00:59:12,660 --> 00:59:15,858
There are lots of animals.
Sure, no problem.

884
00:59:16,580 --> 00:59:18,014
Want to be a squirrel?

885
00:59:18,140 --> 00:59:19,893
No, I don't play animals.

886
00:59:22,060 --> 00:59:25,895
Well... Sure you don't mind,
half way through the term?

887
00:59:26,020 --> 00:59:27,977
No! Just the opposite.

888
00:59:28,100 --> 00:59:30,899
No, I need a flower.
I need a squirrel.

889
00:59:31,020 --> 00:59:33,660
My mushroom shows up
only half the time.

890
00:59:34,840 --> 00:59:35,910
See you Wednesday?

891
00:59:36,040 --> 00:59:38,475
- Yes, thanks.
- My pleasure.

892
00:59:38,600 --> 00:59:40,114
Well... goodbye.

893
00:59:40,240 --> 00:59:41,230
Goodbye, girls!

894
00:59:41,360 --> 00:59:42,350
Time to go!

895
01:00:37,200 --> 01:00:40,671
The worst is when even close friends
start to have doubts.

896
01:00:40,800 --> 01:00:43,110
Maybe they're not that close.

897
01:00:44,520 --> 01:00:46,113
It's understandable.

898
01:00:46,240 --> 01:00:48,709
So tempting to join the pack.

899
01:00:52,260 --> 01:00:53,979
And he's not even polluting.

900
01:00:54,100 --> 01:00:55,250
There you are!

901
01:00:55,820 --> 01:00:57,812
One more reason not to worry.

902
01:00:59,580 --> 01:01:01,378
Rumours pass.

903
01:01:02,340 --> 01:01:03,979
People will tire of it.

904
01:01:12,180 --> 01:01:14,297
That's what made you so sad?

905
01:01:17,820 --> 01:01:19,174
Yes. Well...

906
01:01:20,900 --> 01:01:22,573
Life in general.

907
01:01:25,680 --> 01:01:27,592
These days, I don't know...

908
01:01:30,920 --> 01:01:32,320
it's complicated.

909
01:01:35,460 --> 01:01:36,974
True, it's complicated.

910
01:01:41,320 --> 01:01:43,710
Oh, Maxime! You here?

911
01:01:46,740 --> 01:01:48,459
- Hi.
- How are you?

912
01:01:48,580 --> 01:01:49,696
Not cold?

913
01:01:49,820 --> 01:01:51,459
SEPARATE AND GROW

914
01:01:53,980 --> 01:01:56,131
GETTING FAMILIAR WITH DEATH

915
01:02:00,180 --> 01:02:01,773
And with your father?

916
01:02:02,980 --> 01:02:04,699
No, with my father it's fine.

917
01:02:05,420 --> 01:02:07,139
He's dead anyway, so...

918
01:02:09,180 --> 01:02:10,660
Want to talk about him?

919
01:02:17,840 --> 01:02:19,479
How'd your father treat you?

920
01:02:19,600 --> 01:02:21,398
No, listen. I said no.

921
01:02:26,920 --> 01:02:28,593
My problem is...

922
01:02:29,600 --> 01:02:31,080
I don't understand.

923
01:02:31,520 --> 01:02:33,000
I don't recognise myself.

924
01:02:33,480 --> 01:02:35,915
I don't buy that shit.
How can it get to me?

925
01:02:36,040 --> 01:02:38,111
That's what I want to know.

926
01:02:42,480 --> 01:02:46,030
Is this the first time
you can't control something?

927
01:02:49,900 --> 01:02:51,129
Look,

928
01:02:52,260 --> 01:02:54,252
I think coming here was a mistake.

929
01:02:55,740 --> 01:02:58,016
I need an answer here and now.

930
01:02:58,140 --> 01:02:59,460
I don't want to...

931
01:03:00,460 --> 01:03:02,179
spend years just...

932
01:03:04,700 --> 01:03:05,929
How much do I owe?

933
01:03:06,060 --> 01:03:07,096
Nothing.

934
01:03:15,860 --> 01:03:16,896
Thank you.

935
01:03:18,220 --> 01:03:19,893
Very good solo, Julian.

936
01:03:20,020 --> 01:03:22,171
From the same place again, please.

937
01:03:57,980 --> 01:04:01,576
So I pushed it, I said,
"why not play it at the festival?"

938
01:04:01,700 --> 01:04:03,259
He said yes, on the spot!

939
01:04:03,780 --> 01:04:05,419
- Horwitz?
- Horwitz!

940
01:04:06,500 --> 01:04:08,139
That's amazing!

941
01:04:09,860 --> 01:04:12,455
Horwitz wants to play my piece?

942
01:04:12,580 --> 01:04:13,900
Holy shit!

943
01:04:15,060 --> 01:04:16,540
He liked it that much?

944
01:04:17,260 --> 01:04:18,899
He might tell you himself.

945
01:04:19,020 --> 01:04:21,251
I gave him your number,
he'll call you.

946
01:04:21,380 --> 01:04:24,452
Holy shit, this is... amazing.
Amazing!

947
01:04:25,980 --> 01:04:27,972
Wait a second.
I don't understand.

948
01:04:28,100 --> 01:04:30,296
The orchestra is full. So he...

949
01:04:30,420 --> 01:04:33,254
He would take the place
of the 1st violin. Got to.

950
01:04:34,160 --> 01:04:35,833
Julien's place?

951
01:04:35,960 --> 01:04:38,156
If his name is Julien, then yes.

952
01:04:38,280 --> 01:04:39,555
- Really?
- Of course.

953
01:04:42,200 --> 01:04:43,839
He's my friend.

954
01:04:43,960 --> 01:04:47,476
Not about your friend.
You want your music to be known?

955
01:04:47,600 --> 01:04:50,434
This is an uncanny break.
You don't get that?

956
01:04:51,260 --> 01:04:52,535
Sure I do.

957
01:04:52,660 --> 01:04:54,652
It was really special today.

958
01:04:54,780 --> 01:04:55,770
Nice of you.

959
01:04:55,900 --> 01:04:57,732
It's not nice, it's what I think.

960
01:04:59,940 --> 01:05:01,420
Great, Sandro.

961
01:05:01,540 --> 01:05:02,860
I'm very happy.

962
01:05:03,340 --> 01:05:04,694
- Very happy.
- Right.

963
01:05:08,340 --> 01:05:09,410
Sandro!

964
01:05:10,500 --> 01:05:12,139
Starting to shape up!

965
01:05:12,660 --> 01:05:13,730
Did Wolff like it?

966
01:05:17,780 --> 01:05:19,851
- You think I'm awful.
- No way.

967
01:05:20,980 --> 01:05:23,256
- I'm ashamed.
- Of what?

968
01:05:23,380 --> 01:05:24,860
I'm in love with Sandro.

969
01:05:24,980 --> 01:05:27,097
I think of someone else,
it's not normal.

970
01:05:27,220 --> 01:05:30,258
Normal or not...
What is normal anyway?

971
01:05:32,120 --> 01:05:33,998
Can't imagine how guilty I feel.

972
01:05:34,120 --> 01:05:37,750
Yes, I imagine it very well.
I ruined my life with that guilt.

973
01:05:42,500 --> 01:05:44,219
He invited me to a party.

974
01:05:44,740 --> 01:05:45,856
Really?

975
01:05:46,580 --> 01:05:48,139
But I'm not going to go.

976
01:08:30,200 --> 01:08:31,475
Fuck...

977
01:08:31,920 --> 01:08:33,559
I have to call Sandro.

978
01:08:33,680 --> 01:08:36,354
I don't know how to tell him.
What do I do?

979
01:08:37,280 --> 01:08:39,636
He left me so many messages,
it's terrible.

980
01:08:41,120 --> 01:08:43,032
Maybe a text message?

981
01:08:43,600 --> 01:08:44,750
Not as harsh.

982
01:08:45,240 --> 01:08:47,118
Well, not as harsh for you.

983
01:08:47,240 --> 01:08:48,833
Eat your apple!

984
01:08:52,720 --> 01:08:54,712
In this light, I see them.

985
01:08:55,540 --> 01:08:56,735
Mum!

986
01:08:57,740 --> 01:08:59,618
My mother says I have wrinkles.

987
01:08:59,740 --> 01:09:01,333
Not wrinkles, fine lines.

988
01:09:01,460 --> 01:09:03,816
- Wrinkles!
- Fine lines.

989
01:09:03,940 --> 01:09:06,853
Come on, she's fabulous.
She's perfect.

990
01:09:07,480 --> 01:09:09,119
Marianne, I know about this.

991
01:09:09,240 --> 01:09:12,119
You have to act early.
The sooner the better.

992
01:09:13,200 --> 01:09:15,920
She can't get a facelift at 24,
that's ludicrous!

993
01:09:16,040 --> 01:09:17,030
I use creams.

994
01:09:17,160 --> 01:09:20,836
It's not a facelift. It's acid
produced by the body, re-injected.

995
01:09:20,960 --> 01:09:23,520
She's 24. She's got time!

996
01:09:23,640 --> 01:09:25,871
She doesn't have to act like you.

997
01:09:26,300 --> 01:09:28,292
Like me? Meaning?

998
01:09:29,480 --> 01:09:30,630
I don't know...

999
01:09:31,680 --> 01:09:32,875
Like you.

1000
01:09:34,680 --> 01:09:36,637
You have stuff done.

1001
01:09:36,760 --> 01:09:38,877
Why? What stuff do I have done?

1002
01:09:40,140 --> 01:09:43,099
I don't know.
I have no idea what you got done.

1003
01:09:44,620 --> 01:09:46,577
You're 62, Fanfan.

1004
01:09:49,340 --> 01:09:51,650
I didn't mean to hurt her feelings.

1005
01:09:52,500 --> 01:09:55,493
- Then why say that?
- I said her age.

1006
01:09:56,100 --> 01:09:57,420
I can't pretend to...

1007
01:10:02,060 --> 01:10:03,892
You think old age is fun?

1008
01:10:04,700 --> 01:10:05,850
What do you mean?

1009
01:10:05,980 --> 01:10:08,370
As an actress, well...

1010
01:10:09,880 --> 01:10:13,476
You like your wrinkles, folds,
sagging flesh?

1011
01:10:13,600 --> 01:10:14,716
You think it's fun?

1012
01:10:16,000 --> 01:10:17,434
No, I don't.

1013
01:10:17,560 --> 01:10:18,994
Neither does she.

1014
01:10:20,620 --> 01:10:21,736
Nobody does.

1015
01:10:21,860 --> 01:10:23,135
It was about Laura.

1016
01:10:25,620 --> 01:10:27,418
We have to go now anyway.

1017
01:10:28,260 --> 01:10:30,650
Nina, stop.
You'll get all marked up.

1018
01:10:31,100 --> 01:10:32,216
Should I drop you?

1019
01:10:32,980 --> 01:10:35,336
No, thanks. We'll walk a little.

1020
01:10:35,460 --> 01:10:37,213
You still don't drive?

1021
01:10:37,980 --> 01:10:39,619
No, I still don't.

1022
01:10:45,220 --> 01:10:46,415
What are you doing?

1023
01:10:46,540 --> 01:10:49,180
The apartment is ready.
I'm starting to pack.

1024
01:10:50,420 --> 01:10:52,651
It's ready? Today is only the 8th.

1025
01:10:52,780 --> 01:10:54,214
Yes, but it's ready.

1026
01:10:55,180 --> 01:10:56,296
Morgane?

1027
01:10:57,660 --> 01:10:59,811
Go get me your sister's bag.

1028
01:10:59,940 --> 01:11:01,215
Why doesn't she go?

1029
01:11:01,340 --> 01:11:03,013
She never does a thing!

1030
01:11:05,780 --> 01:11:07,658
We're leaving tomorrow.

1031
01:11:08,460 --> 01:11:10,372
Tomorrow we'll be gone.

1032
01:11:10,860 --> 01:11:13,295
A relief for you,
and me too actually.

1033
01:11:13,420 --> 01:11:14,774
For everyone.

1034
01:11:14,900 --> 01:11:16,050
But...

1035
01:11:18,340 --> 01:11:19,694
All right.

1036
01:11:20,220 --> 01:11:22,018
That contrite pose is great.

1037
01:11:22,140 --> 01:11:23,540
It's not a pose.

1038
01:11:24,340 --> 01:11:25,615
I'm... surprised.

1039
01:11:25,740 --> 01:11:27,538
A pleasant surprise, isn't it?

1040
01:11:28,800 --> 01:11:30,757
We'll get past this rough period.

1041
01:11:30,880 --> 01:11:32,917
- Rough?
- Oh yes.

1042
01:11:34,140 --> 01:11:36,097
You went through hell and I...

1043
01:11:37,660 --> 01:11:40,334
Thank you. You did us a favour.
You took us in.

1044
01:11:40,460 --> 01:11:42,816
Three people, invading your space.

1045
01:11:44,100 --> 01:11:47,218
It was your idea.
You suggested it.

1046
01:11:48,740 --> 01:11:52,814
I never got why
you were so closed up, so icy.

1047
01:11:53,620 --> 01:11:57,216
I even thought you had
a serious problem, you couldn't share.

1048
01:11:57,340 --> 01:11:58,456
I had one.

1049
01:11:58,580 --> 01:11:59,730
What?

1050
01:12:03,940 --> 01:12:08,059
Nothing, it's silly.
Something... stuck inside my head.

1051
01:12:09,100 --> 01:12:13,458
What? You thought I'd force your hand,
form a new family? That it?

1052
01:12:14,220 --> 01:12:16,291
No. You never talk anyway.

1053
01:12:16,420 --> 01:12:19,811
You're shut tight like a vault.
No one can talk to you.

1054
01:12:23,720 --> 01:12:25,473
Anyway, we'll be gone tomorrow.

1055
01:12:46,780 --> 01:12:48,931
Who is he? Do I know him?

1056
01:12:52,580 --> 01:12:54,060
Oh, I know him!

1057
01:12:54,180 --> 01:12:55,739
I said no.

1058
01:13:10,880 --> 01:13:11,950
Well...

1059
01:13:18,520 --> 01:13:20,591
Rehearsals going well?

1060
01:13:22,800 --> 01:13:24,314
Yeah, fine.

1061
01:13:33,360 --> 01:13:34,999
I'll come get my things.

1062
01:13:38,700 --> 01:13:40,578
I brought them for you.

1063
01:14:14,840 --> 01:14:15,990
You're a funny one.

1064
01:14:16,120 --> 01:14:18,032
These things happen.

1065
01:14:18,160 --> 01:14:19,389
Four days out.

1066
01:14:20,800 --> 01:14:22,393
Go tell the caterer.

1067
01:14:23,560 --> 01:14:26,792
Cancel everything.
Call everyone back. Lovely.

1068
01:14:26,920 --> 01:14:29,196
I know, everything I do is bad.

1069
01:14:29,320 --> 01:14:32,199
You have time, darling.
To fall in love, to...

